    Brennan McFarland\\

    In this exercise we will learn mixtures for the MNIST dataset using the
first two PCs, from Exercise 3, and using the Gaussian Mixture Models
Expectation Maximization from Exercises 1 and 2. We begin by duplicating
the necessary code from the previous exercises for the purpose of
keeping them in separate notebooks:

                 \PY{n}{u} \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{cos}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{t}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{sin}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{t}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}
                 \PY{n}{w} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{c} \PY{o}{*} \PY{n}{eigenVector}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{dot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{diag}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{sqrt}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{eigenValue}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{dot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{u}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}

         \PY{k}{def} \PY{n+nf}{gmmplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{gmm}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}

             \PY{n}{plt}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{scatter}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{:}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+m+mi}{0}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{:}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+m+mi}{1}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{s}\PY{o}{=}\PY{l+m+mi}{4}\PY{p}{)}

                 \PY{n}{plotGaussianModel2D}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{model}\PY{p}{[}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{mean}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{model}\PY{p}{[}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{covariance}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{colorPicker}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{index}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}
\end{Verbatim}


    We also have two new functions, randinitCovariance and randinitMean,
which generate random initial means and covariance matrices for the
purposes of our Gaussian Mixture Model. Randomizing these values is
important because we may have no prior knowledge of the properties of
our data, ie prior guesses of the data clustering and covariance, and we
want to avoid multiple means converging to the same cluster or local
minimum:

    \begin{Verbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
{\color{incolor}In [{\color{incolor}21}]:} \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} randomly pick coordinates as center of Gaussian distribution}
         \PY{k}{def} \PY{n+nf}{randinitMean}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{n}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{drange}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
             \PY{n}{mu} \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{]}
             \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{m} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{n}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
                 \PY{n}{mu}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{append}\PY{p}{(}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{random}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{uniform}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{drange}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{i}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{[}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{MIN}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{drange}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{i}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{[}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{MAX}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)} \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{i} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n+nb}{len}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{drange}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)}
             \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} return inf form of numpy.ndarray}
             \PY{k}{return} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{asarray}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{mu}\PY{p}{)}
\end{Verbatim}


    \begin{Verbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
{\color{incolor}In [{\color{incolor}22}]:} \PY{k}{def} \PY{n+nf}{randinitCovariance}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{n}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
             \PY{n}{sigma} \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{]}
             \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{m} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{n}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
                 \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} randomly pick a direction}
                 \PY{n}{angle} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{random}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{uniform}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{0}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+m+mi}{2} \PY{o}{*} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{pi}\PY{p}{)}
                 \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} create eigen vector with the direction and direction orthogonal to it}
                 \PY{n}{eigenVector} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{asarray}\PY{p}{(}\PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{cos}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{angle}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{sin}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{angle}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,}
                                           \PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{cos}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{angle} \PY{o}{+} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{pi}\PY{o}{/}\PY{l+m+mi}{2}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{sin}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{angle} \PY{o}{+} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{pi}\PY{o}{/}\PY{l+m+mi}{2}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)}
                 \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} randomly generate eigen values}
                 \PY{n}{eigenValue} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n+nb}{abs}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{random}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{normal}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{size}\PY{o}{=}\PY{l+m+mi}{2}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}
                 \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} compose covariance matrix}
                 \PY{n}{sigma}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{append}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{eigenVector}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{T}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{dot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{diag}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{eigenValue}\PY{p}{)}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{dot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{eigenVector}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}
             \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} return in form of numpy.ndarray}
             \PY{k}{return} \PY{n}{np}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{asarray}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{sigma}\PY{p}{)}
\end{Verbatim}


    \begin{Verbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
{\color{incolor}In [{\color{incolor}24}]:} \PY{n}{ndata} \PY{o}{=} \PY{l+m+mi}{1000}
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} randomly pick a subset of data}

    \hypertarget{learning-the-mixture-parameters}{%
\subsection{Learning the Mixture
Parameters}\label{learning-the-mixture-parameters}}

    We start with 10 randomly generated means (since we have 10 classes,
digits 0-9) and 10 randomly generated covariance matrices resulting in
10 randomly shaped and positioned elipses overlaid on the decomposed
data below.

    \begin{Verbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
{\color{incolor}In [{\color{incolor}25}]:} \PY{n}{ngmm} \PY{o}{=} \PY{l+m+mi}{10}
         
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} get information of range on each dimension}
         \PY{n}{dataRange} \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{]}
         \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{i} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{shape}\PY{p}{[}\PY{l+m+mi}{1}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
             \PY{n}{dataRange}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{append}\PY{p}{(}\PY{p}{\PYZob{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{MIN}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{:} \PY{n+nb}{min}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{:}\PY{p}{,}\PY{n}{i}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{MAX}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{:} \PY{n+nb}{max}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{:}\PY{p}{,}\PY{n}{i}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{\PYZcb{}}\PY{p}{)}
             
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} randomly initialize Gaussian mixture model}
         \PY{n}{mu}    \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{randinitMean}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{ngmm}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{dataRange}\PY{p}{)}
         \PY{n}{sigma} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{randinitCovariance}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{ngmm}\PY{p}{)}
         \PY{n}{gmm}   \PY{o}{=} \PY{p}{[}\PY{p}{\PYZob{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{mean}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{:} \PY{n}{mu}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{m}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{covariance}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{:} \PY{n}{sigma}\PY{p}{[}\PY{n}{m}\PY{p}{]}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{l+s+s1}{prior}\PY{l+s+s1}{\PYZsq{}}\PY{p}{:} \PY{l+m+mf}{1.0}\PY{o}{/}\PY{n}{ngmm}\PY{p}{\PYZcb{}} \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{m} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{ngmm}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{]}
         
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} show initial state}
         \PY{n}{gmmplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{gmm}\PY{p}{)}
\end{Verbatim}

    Learning the mixture model parameters is the exact same as with the
faithful dataset (and unfortunately the aforementioned error from
Exercise 2 propagates to here as well). We simply update the posteriors
by calling the expectation function from gmmlib, and feed those
posteriors into the maximization function to best optimize the mean,
covariance matrix, and prior probability for each cluster.

    \begin{Verbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
{\color{incolor}In [{\color{incolor}29}]:} \PY{k+kn}{from} \PY{n+nn}{gmmlib} \PY{k}{import} \PY{n}{expectation}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{maximization}
         
         \PY{n}{gmmcp} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{copy}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{deepcopy}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{gmm}\PY{p}{)}
         
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} create figure}
         \PY{n}{plt}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{figure}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{figsize}\PY{o}{=}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{16}\PY{p}{,} \PY{l+m+mi}{16}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{)}
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} improve model with EM\PYZhy{}Algorithm}
         \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{i} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{8}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
             \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} plot current status}
             \PY{n}{plt}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{subplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{331} \PY{o}{+} \PY{n}{i}\PY{p}{)}
             \PY{n}{gmmplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{gmmcp}\PY{p}{)}
             \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} excute EM\PYZhy{}Algorithm}
             \PY{k}{for} \PY{n}{j} \PY{o+ow}{in} \PY{n+nb}{range}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{5}\PY{p}{)}\PY{p}{:}
                 \PY{n}{posterior} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{expectation}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{gmmcp}\PY{p}{)}
                 \PY{n}{gmmcp} \PY{o}{=} \PY{n}{maximization}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{posterior}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,} \PY{n}{gmmcp}\PY{p}{)}
         \PY{c+c1}{\PYZsh{} plot final status}
         \PY{n}{plt}\PY{o}{.}\PY{n}{subplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{l+m+mi}{339}\PY{p}{)}
         \PY{n}{gmmplot}\PY{p}{(}\PY{n}{data}\PY{p}{,}\PY{n}{gmmcp}\PY{p}{)}
\end{Verbatim}
